evo-openldap: evo-openldap (Evolution OpenLDAP NTLM Support)
evo-openldap:
evo-openldap: OpenLDAP is an open source implementation of the Lightweight
evo-openldap: Directory Access Protocol.  LDAP is a alternative to the X.500
evo-openldap: Directory Access Protocol (DAP). It uses the TCP/IP stack versus
evo-openldap: the overly complex OSI stack.
evo-openldap:
evo-openldap: Evolution OpenLDAP is used to provide authentication for 
evo-openldap: Exchange 2000 and 2003 Servers for Evolution.  This LDAP library has 
evo-openldap: been patched for NTLM support.
evo-openldap:
